What am I missing? Druids and shamans get healing spells a full spell circle or more later than clerics. In the lower levels, their utility spells can make up for their <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> lesser</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> healing abilties.<br>
<br>
It could be said that shaman slow and haste can make up the difference in healing abilities between them and clerics, but at no point are druids better healers than clerics.<br>
<br>
Not to hijack the thread, but I'm curious how Noonie got that conclusion.<br>
<br>
